  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Natural stone sustainability programme India</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project partners would like to perform a Due Diligence of their suppliers of natural stone products from India. An impact assessment will be executed to determine the CSR risks in 5 factories and  1 quarry and underlying root with focus on labor circumstances and health &amp; safety risks.  Based on the outcome of the impact assessment mitigating measures will be taken. The first initial idea is to organize workers through establishing labor committees. Furthermore one of  the focus points will be the vulnerable position of the migrant workers. Awareness on rights and entitlements of migrants needs to be build. The health and safety improvements for workers will be another aspect of the project. Lastly, the implementation of CSR and purchasing policies of the three European project partners will be assessed and improved based upon the identified risks.</narrative>
  </description>
